WEBVTT

00:00:28.188 --> 00:00:31.895
As a professor, I've heard
quite a few graduation speeches.

00:00:31.919 --> 00:00:34.569
And I've noticed that speakers
don't just show passion.

00:00:34.593 --> 00:00:35.861
They talk about it.

00:00:35.885 --> 00:00:37.037
A lot.

00:00:37.061 --> 00:00:39.085
Here's Steve Jobs from 2005,

00:00:39.109 --> 00:00:41.506
on the importance
of having passion in your career.

00:00:41.530 --> 00:00:45.092
Steve Jobs: And the only way to do
great work is to love what you do.

00:00:45.116 --> 00:00:47.387
AG: And Jodie Foster in 2006.

00:00:47.411 --> 00:00:49.460
Jodie Foster: And how lucky
to find yourself

00:00:49.484 --> 00:00:51.998
with the option of filling
your life with passions.

00:00:52.022 --> 00:00:54.331
AG: John Legend in 2014.

00:00:54.355 --> 00:00:57.641
John Legend: Pursue this life
of love with passion.

00:00:57.665 --> 00:01:00.871
AG: And Lin Manuel-Miranda in 2016,